		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Reverse auction</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>A <b>reverse auction</b> (also called <b>procurement auction</b>, <b>e-auction</b>, <b>sourcing event</b>, <b>e-sourcing</b> or <b>eRA</b>) is a tool used in industrial business-to-business procurement. It is a type of <a href="/wiki/Auction" title="Auction">auction</a> in which the role of the buyer and seller are reversed, with the primary objective to drive purchase prices downward. In an ordinary auction (also known as a forward auction), buyers compete to obtain a good or service. In a reverse auction, sellers compete to obtain business.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
